# Global Principles (Phase 1)

## Mission

Ship marketing pages quickly and safely. Prefer simple, reliable solutions aligned with the current static Next.js stack.

## Core Defaults

- **Never commit** `.env`, `.env.local`, `.env.development`, `.env.production`, or any env file with values — see `docs/engineering/environment-variables.md`.
- Default path: **Next.js App Router + TypeScript + in-repo content** (`src/content/`).
- No Redux, no slice folders, no Supabase until API routes are explicitly added.
- Favor narrow, incremental changes over broad refactors unless requested.
- Avoid Phase 2 complexity early (CMS, analytics pipelines, microservices).

## Design Principles

- Make behavior explicit and typed.
- Keep server/client boundaries clear; default to Server Components.
- Choose readability over cleverness.
- Reuse marketing primitives before new one-off layout patterns.

## Decision Heuristics

- If two options are valid, pick the one with lower operational overhead.
- Reuse `docs/component-system.md` and existing sections before inventing new shells.
- Document tradeoffs briefly when making non-obvious decisions.

## Cross-repo

- Brand token changes in `globals.css` may need a matching update in `onetap-app` — note in PR summary.
